				<h2>How do I respond to Mod question?</h2>
<p>I flagged <a href="https://apple.stackexchange.com/a/272082/88313">an answer</a> as abusive because of the derogatory language the author used to reference another user (the answer has since been edited but you can see the original text in the edit history).  I was using <a href="https://meta.stackexchange.com/questions/58032/what-are-the-spam-and-rude-or-abusive-offensive-flags-and-how-do-they-wor/58035#58035">this post</a> as my guide for what constitutes 'abuse'.</p>

<p>The flag reviewer responded with a question to me:
<a href="https://i.stack.imgur.com/hoDQi.png" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><img src="https://i.stack.imgur.com/hoDQi.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>

<p>I don't want the reviewer to think I'm an idiot and I want them to know why I flagged it as I did (I don't want to argue that it was declined, that's within their right).</p>

<p>How do I respond and answer the question?</p>

